[{"id":"VR718508","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a block in two positions on a horizontal surface. The block is attached to one end of a horizontal spring, and the other end of the spring is attached to a wall. In one position, the spring length is 0.28 meters, and the kinetic energy of the block is 4.0 joules and the potential energy of the spring is 0.0 joules. In the other position, the spring length is 0.24 meters, and the kinetic energy of the block is 3.0 joules. A note indicates that the figures are not drawn to scale.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR718508.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A block on a horizontal surface is attached to one end of a spring, and the other end of the spring is attached to a fixed wall, as shown in the figure. The block oscillates with negligible friction on the horizontal surface. When the spring length is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.28 meters\"><math alttext=\"0.28 meters\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>0.28</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>m</mtext></mstyle></math></span></span>, the potential energy of the spring is zero, and the kinetic energy of the block is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4.0 joules\"><math alttext=\"4.0 joules\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>4.0</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>J</mtext></mstyle></math></span></span>. A short time later, when the spring length is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.24 meters\"><math alttext=\"0.24 meters\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0.24</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>m</mtext></math></span></span>, the kinetic energy of the block is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3.0 joules\"><math alttext=\"3.0 joules\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3.0</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>J</mtext></math></span></span>. What is the minimum length of the spring during an oscillation cycle of the block?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR718508_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.08 meters\"><math alttext=\"0.08 meters\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0.08</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>m</mtext></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.12 meters\"><math alttext=\"0.12 meters\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0.12</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>m</mtext></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.16 meters\"><math alttext=\"0.16 meters\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0.16</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>m</mtext></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.20 meters\"><math alttext=\"0.20 meters\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0.20</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>m</mtext></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":3}]